text: Coyle is an unincorporated community in Jefferson County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Coyle was established in 1908, and remained in operation until 1928. The community was named after George Coyle, an early settler. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Jefferson County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Coyle, Washington
